capability.name: documents saved in the Xcode 8 format

label.string:
A play consists of the time before a tackle, pulling the ball carrier's flag, is made.
The ball can be advanced either by a forward pass and catch, or simply running with the ball.

label.text: A six point touchdown is scored when the ball carrier either catches the ball in the endzone or runs it in.

label.string:
After a touchdown is scored, an extra point can be attempted from 5 yards out of the endzone, or an extra two points scored from 10 yards from the endzone.
The same rules for scoring a touchdown apply again here.

label.text: The Quarterback is the first player to receive the ball and is allowed to throw the ball from behind where the ball is snapped.
The Wide Receivers run routes and try to get open to catch the ball.

label.string: The Center snaps the ball to the Quarterback to start a play before running a route and tries to get open to catch the ball too.
Cornerbacks follow the opposing wide receivers and attempt to prevent them from catching the ball or intercept the ball themselves.

label.text: Safeties are similar to cornerbacks however they are positioned deep down the field and are the last line of defence.
The Blitzer attempts to tackle the Quarterback before they are able to throw the ball.

label.string:
The Field is seperated into two halves, with a line marking the middle of the field.
At each end is an "Endzone", which a team must make it into the opposing endzone to score whilst the other team protects their endzone.

A team has four attempts to progress the ball across the midfield line from their own endzone. Then another four attempts to score.
Should a team run out of chances, then the other team starts from their endzone.
